  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nECDSA exists in two variants:\r\n1) The original proposed standard, which uses a random element in its calculation. This means that signing the same data with the same private key several times, creates different results each time.\r\n2) [RFC 6979](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6979#section-3.2) proposes a deterministic variant, which uses HMAC to replace the random element.\r\n\r\nThe SECP256K1 implementation in Besu uses the deterministic variant. When SECP256R1 was implemented, the same variant was used. However, the deterministic variant is not NIST-approved. Besu should use the non-deterministic variant. This matches the native implementation (OpenSSL) that we are using as well.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* When using SECP256K1, the deterministic K calculation should be used\r\n* When using SECP256R1, the non-deterministic K calculation should be used",
